You can customize your keyboard shortcuts. Check out [https://www.masteringemacs.org/article/mastering-key-bindings-emacs Mastering Key Bindings in Emacs - Mastering Emacs] for a tutorial.

In general:

# Use <tt>M-x global-set-key</tt></b>
# Press the '''[[key sequence]]''' you want to bind
# Type the name of the command to be bound to the key sequence
# To save your keybinding so that it will work whenever you start Emacs:
## Recall the previous command with <tt>C-x ESC ESC</tt> (`repeat-complex-command').  It will show you the full Lisp command which does the binding.
## Copy the output you see by using `C-a' to go to the beginning of the line and `C-k' (`kill') to cut the text.
## Paste the text into your InitFile. Save the file.

Package authors: For help on using or choosing keybindings, see CommonlyUsedKeybindings. -- JoeBloggs

